Done. Here's what was changed:

**`earnings-panel.tsx`** — removed the Tailwind CSS 4 CSS-variable pattern (`w-(--progress)` + `style={{ '--progress': ... } as React.CSSProperties}`) in favor of `style={{ width: `${rate}%` }}` directly on the inner div. Also removed the now-unused `import type React from "react"`.

**`sponsor-invitation-email.tsx`** — left unchanged. Email templates sent via Resend's `react:` property require inline styles for cross-client email rendering. `@react-email/components` is not installed, and `react-email` v5.2.9 is a preview CLI only. Removing the inline styles would break email rendering in Outlook, Gmail, and other clients.
